cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.SD 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with the emergence of linguistic phenomena in multi-agent communication games. It also involves the use of deep reinforcement learning for training the agents, which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the social exchanges between the agents, which could be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Sound). Finally, the paper involves the study of emergent properties, which could be categorized under cs.LG (Learning).
